The paper deals with the automated detection and classification of cryptographic algorithms in binary programs using machine learning. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it aims to combat malware and other threats that use cryptographic algorithms to disguise their actions. The use of machine learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for further work to apply these techniques to real-world examples, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
